--- title: "Quarto 572 HW" format: html editor: visual --- ## Project Beginning In this project , we have experimented with different quarto settings, and analysed a data set named "Popular Kids" ## Running Code When you click the **Render** button a document will be generated that includes both content and the output of embedded code. You can embed code like this: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} library(foreign) library(ggplot2) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` Warning: package 'ggplot2' was built under R version 4.2.3 ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} library(DT) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` Warning: package 'DT' was built under R version 4.2.3 ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} setwd(here::here()) dataset=read.arff("PopularKids.arff") ``` ::: You can add options to executable code like this ::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](index3_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-2-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: The `echo: false` option disables the printing of code (only output is displayed). ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} result <- kruskal.test(Grades ~ Goals, data = dataset) # Print the test result print(result) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test data: Grades by Goals Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 22.22, df = 2, p-value = 1.496e-05 ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} means <- aggregate(Grades ~ Goals, data = dataset, FUN = mean) # Print the means print(means) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` Goals Grades 1 Grades 2.392713 2 Popular 2.914894 3 Sports 2.766667 ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} means <- aggregate(. ~ Goals, data = dataset[, c("Goals", "Grades", "Sports", "Looks", "Money")], FUN = mean) means_rounded <- means means_rounded[, -1] <- round(means[, -1], digits = 1) datatable(means_rounded) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} a=table(dataset$Gender,dataset$Goals) df=as.matrix(a) colnames(df) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` [1] "Grades" "Popular" "Sports" ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} rownames(df) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` [1] "boy" "girl" ``` ::: ```{.r .cell-code} data_frame=rbind(c("",colnames(df)),c("boy",df[1,1:3]),c("girl",df[2,1:3])) datatable(data_frame) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
